ptMonSysName.name: ptMonSysName
ptMonSysName.reference: This object contains a value identical to that of the MIB-II sysName object.
ptMonSysName.description: An administratively assigned name for the videoconferencing system. If the name is unknown, the value contained in this object is the zero-length string. This value is the same as the system name defined in the system software.

ptMonSysDescription.name: ptMonSysDescription
ptMonSysDescription.reference: This object contains a value identical to that of the MIB-II sysDescr object.
ptMonSysDescription.description: A textual description of the videoconferencing system. The value is a string containing the vendor name, the product name, and the product version. Here is an example: `PictureTel Venue 2000 version 1.3'.

ptMonSysOID.name: ptMonSysOID
ptMonSysOID.reference: This object contains a value identical to that of the MIB-II sysObjectID object.
ptMonSysOID.description: The product identifier for the PictureTel system. The value of this managed object is an Object Value Assignment (OVA), residing within the registration subtree of the vendor's enterprise name space. This object is useful in verifying the model and version of the vendor's service.

ptMonSysUpTime.name: ptMonSysUpTime
ptMonSysUpTime.reference: This object contains a value identical to that contained in the MIB-II sysUpTime object.
ptMonSysUpTime.description: The elapsed time since the PictureTel SNMP agent was started.

ptMonSysContact.name: ptMonSysContact
ptMonSysContact.reference: This object contains a value identical to that contained in the MIB-II sysContact object.
ptMonSysContact.description: The textual identification of the on-site support staff responsible for the videoconferencing system installation. If no contact information is known, the value contained in this object is the zero-length string.

ptMonSysLocation.name: ptMonSysLocation
ptMonSysLocation.reference: This object contains a value identical to that of the MIB-II sysLocation object.
ptMonSysLocation.description: The physical location of the videoconferencing system (e.g., `Main conference room - 3rd floor'). If the location is unknown, the value contained in this object is the zero-length string.
